# Authorship Standards

**REQUIRED:** Every file must include authorship attribution.

---

## Documentation Files (.md, .html, dashboards, monitors)

Add a **footer** at the end of the file:

```markdown
---

Maintained by: Charley (@charleymm)
Last Updated: YYYY-MM-DD
```

For HTML dashboards/monitors, add before closing `</body>`:

```html
<!-- Maintained by: Charley (@charleymm) | Last Updated: YYYY-MM-DD -->
```

---

## Code Files (.js, .ts, .py, .sh, .ps1, etc.)

Add a **header** at the beginning of the file:

### JavaScript/TypeScript

```javascript
/**
 * @file filename.js
 * @description Brief description of the file's purpose
 * @author Charley (@charleymm)
 * @created YYYY-MM-DD
 * @updated YYYY-MM-DD
 */
```

### Python

```python
"""
filename.py
Brief description of the file's purpose

Author: Charley (@charleymm)
Created: YYYY-MM-DD
Updated: YYYY-MM-DD
"""
```

### Bash/Shell Scripts

```bash
#!/bin/bash
# ============================================================================
# filename.sh
# Brief description of the file's purpose
# ============================================================================
# Author:      Charley (@charleymm)
# Created:     YYYY-MM-DD
# Updated:     YYYY-MM-DD
# ============================================================================
```

### PowerShell

```powershell
<#
.SYNOPSIS
    Brief description of the script's purpose
.DESCRIPTION
    More detailed description
.AUTHOR
    Charley (@charleymm)
.CREATED
    YYYY-MM-DD
.UPDATED
    YYYY-MM-DD
#>
```

